---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../components/Callout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Maine Dispensary Profitability Guide | Interactive ROI Tool" description="Beginner-friendly tool for understanding Maine cannabis dispensary finances. Learn about margins, taxes, overhead, and COGS.">
  <section class="calculator-header">
    <div class="hero-badge">Founder's Financial Roadmap</div>
    <h1>Maine Dispensary Success Calculator</h1>
    <p class="lead">We've simplified the complex world of cannabis finance into a "Business Flight Simulator." Let's map out your path to profitability.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="calc-container">
    <div class="calc-inputs">
      <div class="input-section">
        <h2>1. Your Launch Fund</h2>
        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="capital">How much money are you starting with?</label>
          <div class="currency-input">
            <span>$</span>
            <input type="number" id="capital" value="100000" step="5000" />
          </div>
          <p class="input-hint">Includes your license, store design, and first batch of product.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="input-section">
        <h2>2. Daily Sales Goals</h2>
        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="customers">Estimated Customers per Month:</label>
          <input type="range" id="customers" min="100" max="5000" value="800" class="slider" />
          <div class="slider-value"><span id="customer-count">800</span> shoppers</div>
        </div>
        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="avg-sale">Average Customer Spend:</label>
          <div class="currency-input small">
            <span>$</span>
            <input type="number" id="avg-sale" value="85" step="5" />
          </div>
          <p class="input-hint">Maine's average is around $80-$95 per visit.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="input-section">
        <h2>3. Keeping the Lights On (OPEX)</h2>
        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="expenses">Monthly Bills (Rent, Payroll, Power):</label>
          <div class="currency-input small">
            <span>$</span>
            <input type="number" id="expenses" value="20000" step="1000" />
          </div>
          <p class="input-hint">Total monthly operating expenses (OPEX).</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="calc-results">
      <div class="result-card primary" id="profit-card">
        <span class="result-label">Your Monthly Take-Home</span>
        <span class="result-value" id="monthly-profit">Calculating...</span>
        
        <!-- Profitability Gauge -->
        <div class="gauge-container">
          <div id="gauge-bar" class="gauge-bar"></div>
          <div class="gauge-markers">
            <span>Loss</span>
            <span>Break-Even</span>
            <span>Growth</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p id="profit-status">Your projected monthly profit after all costs.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="result-grid">
        <div class="result-card">
          <span class="result-label">Yearly Revenue</span>
          <span class="result-value small" id="annual-revenue">...</span>
        </div>
        <div class="result-card">
          <span class="result-label">Time to Pay Yourself Back</span>
          <span class="result-value small" id="breakeven">...</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="optimization-advice" class="optimization-box hidden">
        <h4>💡 Mentor's Advice for Growth:</h4>
        <p id="advice-text"></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="how-it-works">
    <h2>How the Success Calculator Works</h2>
    <p>To give you a realistic picture, our calculator follows the actual path of a dollar in a Maine dispensary. Here is the step-by-step breakdown of the math:</p>
    
    <div class="math-steps">
      <div class="step-box">
        <div class="step-num">1</div>
        <div class="step-text">
          <h3>Total Revenue</h3>
          <p>We start by multiplying your <strong>Customers</strong> by your <strong>Average Sale</strong>. This is the total money that enters your register.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step-box">
        <div class="step-num">2</div>
        <div class="step-text">
          <h3>Subtract COGS</h3>
          <p>Next, we subtract the <strong><a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-costs/">COGS (Cost of Goods Sold)</a></strong>. In Maine, this is roughly <strong>65%</strong> of your revenue—the money you pay to cultivators and manufacturers for the products on your shelf.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step-box">
        <div class="step-num">3</div>
        <div class="step-text">
          <h3>Subtract 280E Taxes</h3>
          <p>We then account for <strong><a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-taxation-280e/">280E</a></strong>. This is a federal tax rule that prevents cannabis shops from taking standard deductions. We set aside roughly <strong>21%</strong> of your Gross Profit for the IRS to keep you compliant.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step-box">
        <div class="step-num">4</div>
        <div class="step-text">
          <h3>Subtract OPEX</h3>
          <p>Finally, we subtract your <strong><a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-costs/">OPEX (Operating Expenses)</a></strong>. These are your "Monthly Bills" like rent, payroll, and utilities. What's left over is your <strong>Net Monthly Profit</strong>—your real take-home pay!</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="financial-glossary">
    <h2>Financial Terms Simplified</h2>
    <div class="glossary-grid">
      <div class="glossary-box">
        <h3>COGS (Cost of Product)</h3>
        <p>The money you spend to buy inventory. If you sell an eighth for $40 and you bought it from a grower for $20, your COGS is $20.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="glossary-box">
        <h3>280E (The "Federal Burden")</h3>
        <p>A federal tax code that treats cannabis revenue differently. It makes your effective tax rate much higher than a normal "Main Street" business.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="glossary-box">
        <h3>OPEX (Operating Expenses)</h3>
        <p>Your "Monthly Burn Rate." This includes everything it takes to run the shop: rent, payroll, insurance, and electricity.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script is:inline>
    function calculate() {
      const capital = parseFloat(document.getElementById('capital').value) || 0;
      const customers = parseInt(document.getElementById('customers').value);
      const avgSale = parseFloat(document.getElementById('avg-sale').value) || 0;
      const opex = parseFloat(document.getElementById('expenses').value) || 0;
      
      const customerCountDisplay = document.getElementById('customer-count');
      if (customerCountDisplay) customerCountDisplay.innerText = customers;

      const monthlyGrossRev = customers * avgSale;
      const annualRev = monthlyGrossRev * 12;
      const cogs = monthlyGrossRev * 0.65;
      const grossProfit = monthlyGrossRev - cogs;
      const tax280e = grossProfit * 0.21;
      const netMonthlyProfit = grossProfit - tax280e - opex;
      const monthsToBreakeven = netMonthlyProfit > 0 ? Math.ceil(capital / netMonthlyProfit) : -1;

      const formatter = new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US', { style: 'currency', currency: 'USD', maximumFractionDigits: 0 });
      
      const profitDisplay = document.getElementById('monthly-profit');
      const revenueDisplay = document.getElementById('annual-revenue');
      const breakevenEl = document.getElementById('breakeven');
      const adviceBox = document.getElementById('optimization-advice');
      const adviceText = document.getElementById('advice-text');
      const profitCard = document.getElementById('profit-card');
      const gaugeBar = document.getElementById('gauge-bar');

      if (profitDisplay) profitDisplay.innerText = formatter.format(netMonthlyProfit);
      if (revenueDisplay) revenueDisplay.innerText = formatter.format(annualRev);
      
      if (adviceBox) adviceBox.classList.remove('hidden');

      if (netMonthlyProfit <= 0) {
        if (breakevenEl) breakevenEl.innerText = "Check Advice Below";
        if (profitCard) profitCard.style.background = "#8B0000";
        if (gaugeBar) {
          gaugeBar.style.width = "15%";
          gaugeBar.style.background = "#ff6b6b";
        }
        if (adviceText) adviceText.innerHTML = "<strong>Don't get discouraged!</strong> This scenario shows a net loss. To turn this into a profit, try <strong>increasing your average customer spend by $10</strong> or finding a more affordable location to <strong>reduce your OPEX (Monthly Bills)</strong>.";
      } else {
        if (profitCard) profitCard.style.background = "var(--color-primary)";
        if (gaugeBar) {
          gaugeBar.style.width = Math.min(100, 50 + (netMonthlyProfit / 1000)) + "%";
          gaugeBar.style.background = "#A3B18A";
        }
        if (breakevenEl) breakevenEl.innerText = monthsToBreakeven > 60 ? "5+ Years" : monthsToBreakeven + " Months";
        if (adviceText) adviceText.innerHTML = "<strong>You're on the right track!</strong> You are covering your <strong>OPEX</strong> and <strong>280E</strong> taxes. To reach your goals even faster, focus on building a <strong>Loyalty Program</strong> to increase your customer return rate.";
      }
    }

    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      const inputs = ['capital', 'customers', 'avg-sale', 'expenses'];
      inputs.forEach(id => {
        const el = document.getElementById(id);
        if(el) el.addEventListener('input', calculate);
      });
      calculate();
    });
    calculate();
  </script>
</Layout>

<style>
  .calculator-header { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 4rem; position: relative; z-index: 10; }
  .hero-badge { display: inline-block; background: var(--color-primary); color: white; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; border-radius: 2rem; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .lead { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto; }

  .calc-container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    margin-bottom: 6rem;
    background: white;
    padding: 4rem;
    border-radius: 2rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    box-shadow: 0 20px 50px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);
    position: relative;
    z-index: 10;
  }

  .input-section { margin-bottom: 3rem; padding-bottom: 2rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-background); }
  .input-section h2 { font-size: 1rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .input-group label { display: block; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.95rem; }

  .currency-input { display: flex; align-items: center; font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-primary); border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-primary); }
  .currency-input.small { font-size: 1.5rem; }
  .currency-input input { border: none; padding: 0.5rem; width: 100%; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-primary); background: transparent; }
  .currency-input input:focus { outline: none; }

  .slider { width: 100%; height: 6px; background: var(--color-background); border-radius: 3px; appearance: none; outline: none; }
  .slider::-webkit-slider-thumb { appearance: none; width: 24px; height: 24px; background: var(--color-primary); border-radius: 50%; cursor: pointer; }
  .slider-value { margin-top: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-primary); font-size: 0.9rem; }

  .calc-results { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }
  .result-card { background: var(--color-background); padding: 2.5rem; border-radius: 1.5rem; text-align: center; transition: background 0.3s; }
  .result-card.primary { background: var(--color-primary); color: white; }
  .result-label { display: block; font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.1em; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; opacity: 0.8; }
  .result-value { display: block; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 3.5rem; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .result-value.small { font-size: 2.25rem; }
  .result-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; }

  /* Profitability Gauge */
  .gauge-container { width: 100%; height: 8px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.2); border-radius: 4px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; position: relative; }
  .gauge-bar { height: 100%; width: 50%; background: #588157; border-radius: 4px; transition: all 0.6s cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1); }
  .gauge-markers { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; font-size: 0.65rem; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 800; margin-top: 0.5rem; opacity: 0.7; }

  .optimization-box { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.1); padding: 2rem; border-radius: 1.5rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-accent); margin-top: 1rem; }
  .optimization-box h4 { margin-top: 0; color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .optimization-box p { margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; }
  .hidden { display: none; }

  .how-it-works { margin-bottom: 6rem; position: relative; z-index: 10; }
  .math-steps { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; margin-top: 2.5rem; }
  .step-box { display: flex; gap: 2rem; align-items: flex-start; padding: 2rem; background: white; border-radius: 1.5rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .step-num { width: 40px; height: 40px; background: var(--color-primary); color: white; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: 800; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .step-text h3 { margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--color-primary); font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .step-text p { margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }

  .financial-glossary { margin-bottom: 6rem; position: relative; z-index: 10; }
  .glossary-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: 2rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .glossary-box { background: white; padding: 2rem; border-radius: 1.5rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .glossary-box h3 { margin-top: 0; color: var(--color-primary); font-size: 1.15rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .glossary-box p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-text-light); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0; }

  @media (max-width: 1000px) { .calc-container { grid-template-columns: 1fr; padding: 2rem; } }
</style>
